content: Beautiful cute, amazing story with fun character development and personality. This is quite simply a 10 star app!

This game is awesome. One of my favorites. One thing I was disappointed by though, is that killing the Dark Lord with the shotgun doesn't count as an ending. replyContent:
How did you manage to get to him with the shotgun? :O

Well, here's an ending for you:
"After killing the Dark Lord, Tim felt somehow dead inside. With no nemesis to fight him, resuing the Princess was no longer a challenge, so he left her to rot in the dungeon." Ending #187/100

content: Totally worth it, every ending was brilliant and the secret ending after getting them all was the cherry on top

Extremely fun and creative at first but gets EXTREMELY repetitive whwn trying to 100% the game and find every ending. I personally despise backtracking in a game and the late game is nothing but backtracking. No new areas, exploration, secrets, or shortcuts at that point, just plain old backtracking. Nevertheless, the first 5 hours were an absolutely enjoyable experience and I recommend it highly to anyone. The game's central idea just starts to wear thin after that point.
replyContent: Yup, we understand. It's kind of impossible to cover all 100 endings without some amount of repetition, but we hope the overall experience was worth it. We have some ideas to fix that in the future though ;)

Great game! At first, I thought it was somewhat too repetitive, but I've had so much fun with it. The world changes as you progress, and there are tons of areas and secrets to find, either cleverly or through luck! I like the graphics and music, but the writing and concept is really what makes it. To my surprise, there were also quite a lot of post-game things to continue forward! All in all, a fun game strewn with dark humor that made me laugh and a big world to explore and figure out!
Very nice!

This game is dope, especially if you suffer from OCD. You will want to keep playing "just another run" before you realize that you've been playing for hours. Graphics, sound/music are serviceable, but the main charm is the writing and the very original game play. Has lots of depth and values the player's time investment. Gets a bit weary towards the end because of the inevitable repetition. Would be nice to see future game with a more nuanced world rather than just a parody of classic games
